Name: Double Helix Wine & Whiskey Lounge
Description: Located just south of The Strip at Town Square Las Vegas, the 2,800-square-foot space features a full bar that offers over 40 unique wines by the glass, 100 whiskey labels, sampler â€¦Learn more about Double Helix Wine & Whiskey Lounge, Opens a popupSpecialtiesLocated just south of The Strip at Town Square Las Vegas, the 2,800-square-foot space features a full bar that offers over 40 unique wines by the glass, 100 whiskey labels, sampler flights, and Double Helix's signature cocktails.Chef Doug Vega, whose previous experience includes Daniel Boulud's DB Brasserie, has created a wine and spirit-friendly small-plates tasting menu. Guests are treated to shareable, melt-in-your-mouth dishes that satisfy any craving for $16 or less. Our diverse menu includes charcuterie and cheese boards, flatbreads, and a range of gourmet comfort food dishes like arancini, steak frites, grown-up grilled cheese, meatballs, a variety of sliders and seared yellowfin tuna. Chef has also added a gluten free menu to our offerings.The pet-friendly and cigar-friendly patio includes a beautiful fire pit conducive for conversation and gatherings, a cooling mister system for the summer, and ultra-comfortable lounge-style furniture. The patio is also available for private tastings and special events. Televisions showing key sporting events are located both inside and on the patio.The award-winning happy hour from 3:30-7:30 pm Monday-Friday and 11 am-7:30 pm Saturday and Sunday feature special priced bites, half off wine and whiskey of the month, $5-7 glasses of wine and $4 beers.HistoryEstablished in 2011.Founded in 2008 by Raymond Nisi, Lucky Metalios and Jonathan Stern, Double Helix launched its first bar concept at The Grand Canal Shoppes at The Palazzo.
